ive before generating metadata? Guidelines indicate tests should run, but perhaps we shouldn't trigger the Report until after metadata generation? It seems the workflow generates external metadata based on tests. \\n\\nAdditionally, I’m considering adding a regular test resource to include minimal keys. Native images include application resources, but I need to clarify how resources are included. I’ll investigate further!\\n\\n**Investigating ResourceBundle loading**\\n\\nI'm trying to confirm that a ResourceBundle with a base name containing a slash can't find the class. It seems that while a slash might be accepted in ClassLoader's loadClass, the Java class name binary shouldn't have one, which likely leads to failure. \\n\\nMaybe if I create a class like `org.w3c.tidy.TidyMessages` and use `ResourceBundle.getBundle(\\\"org/w3c/tidy/TidyMessages\\\")`, it could work, but I'll need to check if `loader.loadClass(bundleName)` is valid. It leads me to think about using a default locale class or instrumenting my native image build to initialize `Report` at build-time.\\n\\n**Evaluating native image constraints**\\n\\nI’m considering if modifying reachability metadata or Native Image config entries could cause a violation. The test doesn’t actually run at runtime, and dynamic coverage from JVM might not be achievable here. It seems the coverage may not be broad enough, so I should avoid it. I wonder if setting a system property during the test could force initialization at build time, but that doesn't seem to work. I'm a bit stuck on how to proceed with using `Report.class` as well.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_05d581b97d6180010169fb949010c08191aa52ce2aa4b4e4f8\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-5Sm2AjXGkYSFyE7IuSACc1ZkDKPhW0VxJEGFuKTPBYApP4jFpfEys870K5HKpnNOIDSKGVJ-J4IIYpnb0iVy2U5dbC1OasRcGW9yrP6bVb-87knhCpXGSKQJn6hJvNHzJZ1TqFnnXlS9E_qHcqOQP10uV5vno46UHmtoq-pbYG9Q2SqZz3SOat6HynsWXlbUCSnCmRnnOnfuLwshi-97tMH666cybR