itialize `Report` at build-time.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating native image constraints**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering if modifying reachability metadata or Native Image config entries could cause a violation. The test doesn’t actually run at runtime, and dynamic coverage from JVM might not be achievable here. It seems the coverage may not be broad enough, so I should avoid it. I wonder if setting a system property during the test could force initialization at build time, but that doesn't seem to work. I'm a bit stuck on how to proceed with using `Report.class` as well.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_hqovkYrGMhTFFFYNELQWQfVs|fc_05d581b97d6180010169fb94a6ec2881918694569296afbef6\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"grep -n '^unknown_option\\\\|^bad_argument' /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/jtidy/jtidy/4aug2000r7-dev/main/extracted/org/w3c/tidy/TidyMessages.properties\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1464, \"output\": 1311, \"cacheRead\": 37888, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 40663, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778095244012, \"responseId\": \"resp_05d581b97d6180010169fb948d7e308191ac23633add9655f7\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_hqovkYrGMhTFFFYNELQWQfVs|fc_05d581b97d6180010169fb94a6ec2881918694569296afbef6\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"125:unknown_option=Warning - unknown option: {0}\\n126:bad_argument=Warning - missing or malformed argument for option: {0}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778095271712}]}\nhuman-intervention-logs/jtidy:jtidy:4aug2000r7-dev/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-06T19-14-50-978743Z.log:2912:[thinking] Ultimately,