-level test classes should be public. Since the developer suggests public status for all top-level tests, it might be worth adjusting JtidyTest, even if it isn't active.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering access modifiers**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking that having the existing package-private access may violate checkstyle rules, even though it passed initially. We could make it public to comply, but it seems like such a small detail. The task is focused on active classes only, so maybe it's better not to emphasize this right now. I probably need to read the current file to get a clearer idea before making any final decisions.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_Gfvz8OzGwGvYSK0FSbSmUxFP|fc_05d581b97d6180010169fb94c4e0b08191a2f4a9c845681c32\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/jtidy/jtidy/4aug2000r7-dev/src/test/java/jtidy/jtidy/ReportTest.java\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1054, \"output\": 522, \"cacheRead\": 40448, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 42024, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778095284644, \"responseId\": \"resp_05d581b97d6180010169fb94b63f5c81918fbfa86abc4279d0\"}}\n2929:[tool-exec] start id=call_Gfvz8OzGwGvYSK0FSbSmUxFP|fc_05d581b97d6180010169fb94c4e0b08191a2f4a9c845681c32 name=read args={\"path\": \"tests/src/jtidy/jtidy/4aug2000r7-dev/src/test/java/jtidy/jtidy/ReportTest.java\"}\n2948:  public class ReportTest {\n2978:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_Gfvz8OzGwGvYSK0FSbSmUxFP|fc_05d581b97d6180010169fb94c4e0b08191a2f4a9c845681c32\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage jtidy.jtidy;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\\nimport java.io.PrintStream;\\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\\n\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\nimport org.w3c.tidy.Report;\\n\\npublic class ReportTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void unknownOptionLoadsReportMessageBundle() {\\n        PrintStream originalErr = System.err;\\n        ByteArrayOutputStream errors = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\\n        System.setErr(new PrintStream(errors, true, StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\\n        try {\\n            Report.unknownOption(\\\"not-a-tidy-option\\\");\\n        } catch (Error error) {\\n            if (isMissingTidyMessagesBundle(error)) {\\n                assertThat(error)\\n                        .hasMessageContaining(\\\"org/w3c/tidy/TidyMessages\\\");\\n                return;\\n            }\\n            throw error;\\n        } finally {\\n            System.setErr(originalErr);\\n        }\\n\\n        assertThat(errors.toString(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))\\n                .contains(\\\"Warning - unknown option: not-a-tidy-option\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    private static boolean isMissingTidyMessagesBundle(Error error) {\\n        String message = error.getMessage();\\n        return message != null\\n                && message.contains(\\\"MissingResourceException\\\")\\n                && message.contains(\\\"org/w3c/tidy/TidyMessages\\\");\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778095301445}}\n2979:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_Gfvz8OzGwGvYSK0FSbSmUxFP|fc_05d581b97d6180010169fb94c4e0b08191a2f4a9c845681c32\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage jtidy.jtidy;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\\nimport java.io.PrintStream;\\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\\n\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\nimport org.w3c.tidy.Report;\\n\\npublic class ReportTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void unknownOptionLoadsReportMessageBundle() {\\n        PrintStream originalErr = System.err;\\n        ByteArrayOutputStream errors = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\\n        System.setErr(new PrintStream(errors, true, StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\\n        try {\\n            Report.unknownOption(\\\"not-a-tidy-option\\\");\\n        } catch (Error error) {\\n            if (isMissingTidyMessagesBundle(error)) {\\n                assertThat(error)\\n                        .hasMessageContaining(\\\"org/w3c/tidy/TidyMessages\\\");\\n                return;\\n            }\\n            throw error;\\n        } finally {\\n            System.setErr(originalErr);\\n        }\\n\\n        assertThat(errors.toString(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))\\n                .contains(\\\"Warning - unknown option: not-a-tidy-option\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    private static boolean isMissingTidyMessagesBundle(Error error) {\\n        String message = error.getMessage();\\n        return message != null\\n                && message.contains(\\\"MissingResourceException\\\")\\n                && message.contains(\\\"org/w3c/tidy/TidyMessages\\\");\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778095301445}}\n2980:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating PrintStream and JVM behavior**\\n\\nI need to think about the `PrintStream(OutputStream, boolean, Charset)` constructor starting from Java 10, and the `ByteArrayOutputStream.toString(Charset)` method, which was also introduced in Java 10. There are two versions: `toString(String charsetName)` and `toString(Charset)`.\\n\\nI might encounter issues with catch Error in checkstyle, but it seems okay for a method that catches Error and uses finally. However, there's this moment of concern with assertion errors before finally runs. If the JVM's class initialization fails, it could result in an ExceptionInInitializerError. \\n\\nUltimately, it seems the user is mostly focused on coverage.\\n\\n**Assessing JtidyTest handling**\\n\\nI’m pondering whether we should keep the JtidyTest placeholder or think about removing it. The rule is to maintain a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and their generated test class files. The existing JtidyTest seems to violate this rule, but it does exist. \\n\\nMaybe it's better to remove the placeholder to focus on active classes, although there’s the concern that modifying this might be unrelated. It makes sense to keep everything tidy, and I’m considering whether all top-level test classes should be public. Since the developer suggests public status for all top-level tests, it might be worth adjusting JtidyTest, even if it isn't active.\\n\\n**Considering access modifiers**\\n\\nI’m thinking that having the existing package-private access may violate checkstyle rules, even though it passed initially. We could make it public to comply, but it seems like such a small detail. The task is focused on active classes only, so maybe it's better not to emphasize this right now. I probably need to read the current file to get a clearer idea before making any final decisions.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_05d581b97d6180010169fb94b780848191adbbf84c894d6ee2\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-5TE1tWFlhTAVlH1Fir0SJMFQ_av_F_xOqPMvHO3GQDPoai_3Fm_OLwRJejNGcReYPf9O8WtsUTyGfpJs8wmaJ-9DXGD3dlPG2RaUeKOnXkqiOl6-ERsOTDZeB1ApqzdnlJ_LVw3-0hJLXwfqopz7Q2_15RCsb0ATp3Yb33djMlkiI4sSX8i0Wpqr-DJxh67xXChVhEtFKVVAAsL9gLhvjGKb3C_aWqsKTYugRVqSK1lZe