inalErr);\\n        }\\n\\n        assertThat(errors.toString(StandardCharsets.UTF_8))\\n                .contains(\\\"Warning - unknown option: not-a-tidy-option\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    private static boolean isMissingTidyMessagesBundle(Error error) {\\n        String message = error.getMessage();\\n        return message != null\\n                && message.contains(\\\"MissingResourceException\\\")\\n                && message.contains(\\\"org/w3c/tidy/TidyMessages\\\");\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778095301445}]}\n2990:[assistant] Updated the dedicated `ReportTest` to exercise `org.w3c.tidy.Report` directly.\n2992:[assistant] Changed:\n2994:[assistant] - `tests/src/jtidy/jtidy/4aug2000r7-dev/src/test/java/jtidy/jtidy/ReportTest.java`\n3004:[assistant] I did not run or compile tests, per instructions.\n3006:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating test results**\\n\\nI'm considering whether it uses native test results, and it seems the native test passes. That's a positive sign! I could include direct output for `Report.unknownOption` to ensure `res.getString` is successful. It might also be a good idea to add an assertion before the return to check if there’s an error stack with `Report.<clinit>`. Although it's not absolutely necessary, verifying the reason sounds good. I should make that final mention more refined!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_05d581b97d6180010169fb94c80070819187504458cf4d5296\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-5TOV0ygYa3_BdHeLF_JpTLsCKq-M3rXj44mUTLjPF8JQm8NoPNzlx-jrer4Lt5unKIJfqF5p4aneo5-fD3YXIgKyhaEB64itlxbrpCrAwQOYssVRSgA4WImuXYqf6XYFr5Xoow69nDtSgtchIvxGXJ1tNK0R1cLABFLvQjVY_LL22gZwaK33ukRUTi4oAhoXFKg6J0Cak7Uc5RBXrBNZ2dgWB93o6QSRL20P-KpmmxMf9d8ePPtYfR55p6sJ0BLenD8vhr0ySABdadZWNtuieIqBS1r96TCcZhGNtNsnigSxAMQNim8FIPV7m9avCUmLMdQuoFtFL_KDTyy5gCf8v2j1YpUp0zipH882qy